          "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"rust-lang/rust\",\n      \"path\": \"compiler/rustc_infer/src/infer/mod.rs\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"rust-lang/rust\",\n      \"path\": \"compiler/rustc_hir_typeck/src/fn_ctxt/mod.rs\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"rust-lang/rust\",\n      \"path\": \"compiler/rustc_infer/src/infer/type_variable.rs\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"rust-lang/rust\",\n      \"path\": \"compiler/rustc_infer/src/infer/mod.rs\",\n      \"symbol\": \"InferCtxt\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"rust-lang/rust\",\n      \"path\": \"compiler/rustc_hir_typeck/src/fn_ctxt/mod.rs\",\n      \"symbol\": \"FnCtxt\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"rust-lang/rust\",\n      \"path\": \"compiler/rustc_infer/src/infer/type_variable.rs\",\n      \"symbol\": \"TypeVariableOrigin\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The Rust compiler's type inference architecture is centered around three key components:\\n\\n1. **InferCtxt** (compiler/rustc_infer/src/infer/mod.rs, line 231): The main inference context struct that manages type inference. It contains InferCtxtInner which holds type variable storage, unification tables, region constraints, and other inference data. InferCtxt is the central hub for all type inference operations in the compiler.\\n\\n2. **FnCtxt** (compiler/rustc_hir_typeck/src/fn_ctxt/mod.rs, line 44): The function-level type checker that performs type inference for function bodies, closures, and const expressions. FnCtxt wraps the InferCtxt and provides function-specific type checking functionality. It tracks return type coercion, divergence information, parameter environments, and enclosing breakable contexts needed for type checking expressions within a function.\\n\\n3. **TypeVariableOrigin** (compiler/rustc_infer/src/infer/type_variable.rs, line 94): A simple struct that tracks the origin of type variables during inference. It contains the span where the type variable was created and optionally the DefId of the type parameter it was instantiated for. This is used for diagnostics to provide better error messages.\\n\\nThe type inference flow works as follows: InferCtxt provides the core unification and constraint solving machinery, while FnCtxt layers on top to provide function-specific context and coordinate the type checking of expressions. TypeVariableOrigin tracks metadata about created type variables for better error reporting.\"\n}\n",
